A police driver attached to Hulugho police station in Garissa county was on Monday night killed when the vehicle he was driving collided head-on with a truck ferrying cows on Madogo-Garissa road. Garissa police boss Aaron Moriasi said the four occupants of the truck were slightly injured in the midnight accident.A mother and her three-year-old daughter were also injured. A colleague of the deceased sustained serious injuries and is admitted at the Garissa County Referral Hospital in stable condition. Moriasi said the officer&rsquo;s body was transported to Nairobi. The cows&rsquo; owner Elias Abdi said the truck left Wajir at 1pm. He lost eight cows worth more than Sh300,000.